ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS
The fusion architecture may have the following issues:
Hypothesis 1: Fusion Layer Not Learning Properly
The lightweight fusion layer may not be weighting the modalities correctly
Thermal_map may be dominating and degrading the good metadata predictions
Hypothesis 2: RF Quality NOT Actually Preserved in Fusion
While metadata-only preserves RF quality (Kappa 0.254)
The fusion path may be re-learning or degrading RF predictions
Need to inspect the fusion architecture more carefully
Hypothesis 3: Thermal_map and Metadata Incompatible
The two modalities may provide conflicting signals
Simple concatenation/fusion may amplify noise
NEXT STEPS RECOMMENDATIONS
Option A: Investigate Fusion Architecture üîç
